※※
# check-sky-trigger-conflicts

Manually-run workflow that finds two or more workflows bound to the SAME non-manual
trigger — same `sky_event` name, same `cron` schedule, or same github event+action+label
— which would all fire together on one event and cause silent duplicate runs and
double spend. Pure bash, no LLM tokens. Exits non-zero if any collision is found.

  (manual run: --var dir)
       │
       ▼
   ┌────────┐  per file: extract its trigger signature
   │ check  │  (sky_event:<name> | cron:<sched> | github:<ev>:<action>:<label>)
   └────────┘  group by signature; any signature on >1 file is a conflict
       │        manual triggers are ignored — they can't collide
       ▼
     report + exit 1 on any conflict

Run it (state which directory to check with --var dir):

  sky run check-sky-trigger-conflicts --var dir=".sky/workflows"

  - dir   directory of .sky files to check — STATE THIS (e.g. .sky/workflows)
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "check-sky-trigger-conflicts"
description = "Detect workflows bound to the same non-manual trigger (sky_event, cron, or github event+action+label) that would all fire together, exit non-zero on collision. Fire via: sky run check-sky-trigger-conflicts --var dir=<path>"
trigger.manual = true
output_style = "terse"
⊕⊕

※※
Step 1 — check. The whole audit in one bash pass. Build a "signature<TAB>file" table
in a /tmp scratch file (so cron schedules, which contain spaces, survive intact), then
group it with awk and print any signature shared by more than one workflow. Each file
contributes at most one signature per trigger kind; manual triggers are skipped.
※※

§check§
bash = "set -e\nif [ ! -d \"$SKY_DIR\" ]; then echo \"[triggers] no such dir: $SKY_DIR\"; exit 1; fi\ntmp=$(mktemp)\nfor f in \"$SKY_DIR\"/*.sky; do\n  [ -e \"$f\" ] || continue\n  base=$(basename \"$f\")\n  ev=$(grep -oE 'trigger\\.sky_event[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\"[^\"]*\"' \"$f\" | head -1 | grep -oE '\"[^\"]*\"' | tr -d '\"')\n  [ -n \"$ev\" ] && printf 'sky_event:%s\\t%s\\n' \"$ev\" \"$base\" >> \"$tmp\"\n  cr=$(grep -oE 'trigger\\.cron[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\"[^\"]*\"' \"$f\" | head -1 | grep -oE '\"[^\"]*\"' | tr -d '\"')\n  [ -n \"$cr\" ] && printf 'cron:%s\\t%s\\n' \"$cr\" \"$base\" >> \"$tmp\"\n  ge=$(grep -oE 'trigger\\.github\\.event[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\"[^\"]*\"' \"$f\" | head -1 | grep -oE '\"[^\"]*\"' | tr -d '\"')\n  if [ -n \"$ge\" ]; then\n    ac=$(grep -oE 'trigger\\.github\\.action[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\"[^\"]*\"' \"$f\" | head -1 | grep -oE '\"[^\"]*\"' | tr -d '\"')\n    lb=$(grep -oE 'trigger\\.github\\.label[[:space:]]*=[[:space:]]*\"[^\"]*\"' \"$f\" | head -1 | grep -oE '\"[^\"]*\"' | tr -d '\"')\n    printf 'github:%s:%s:%s\\t%s\\n' \"$ge\" \"$ac\" \"$lb\" \"$base\" >> \"$tmp\"\n  fi\ndone\nbindings=$(wc -l < \"$tmp\" | tr -d ' ')\nreport=$(awk -F'\\t' '{cnt[$1]++; files[$1]=files[$1]\"\\n    \"$2} END{for (s in cnt) if (cnt[s] > 1) print \"CONFLICT  \" s files[s]}' \"$tmp\")\nrm \"$tmp\"\necho \"[triggers] checked $bindings non-manual trigger binding(s)\"\nif [ -n \"$report\" ]; then printf '%s\\n' \"$report\"; echo \"[triggers] conflicting trigger signature(s) found\"; exit 1; fi\necho \"[triggers] no conflicts\""
§§
